# Cloudflare Pages — SPA fallback.
#
# /api/*       — return real 404 instead of the SPA shell so a
#                mis-pointed frontend doesn't silently receive
#                index.html (HTTP 200) in place of a proper 404.
#                Without this, axios treats the SPA shell as JSON
#                and every page breaks with "s?.filter is not a function".
# /assets/*    — same: return real 404 for missing hashed chunks
#                instead of falling back to index.html. The previous
#                catch-all caused stale browsers (with an older
#                index.html cached) to request a chunk hash that no
#                longer exists, receive HTML, and refuse to execute
#                it as a module ("Expected a JS module but got
#                text/html"). A real 404 lets the browser bubble
#                the error up to the dynamic-import call site so
#                we can prompt the user to reload.
# /*           — every other route falls through to the SPA shell.
/api/*        /api/:splat       404
/assets/*     /assets/:splat    404
/*            /index.html       200
